snippet.title: NZ vs WI | 1st T20I | Highlights | West Indies Tour Of New Zealand 2025
snippet.description:
West Indies defeated New Zealand by 7 runs in the first T20I at Eden Park in Auckland on November 5, 2025. New Zealand captain Mitchell Santner's half-century ultimately went in vain as the West Indies bowlers successfully defended their total. Matthew Forde was impressive with the ball early on, while Romario Shepherd held his nerve in the final over to secure the win for the West Indies.

It's Ashes squad selection day in Australia, and it's likely that most cricketing headlines will revolve around who's made the final cut for Perth. Unless you're here on the Gold Coas

After a washout in Canberra, we've seen two pretty high-octane T20Is in Melbourne and Hobart. If Australia were the one who steamrolled India at the MCG courtesy an all-time great T20I spell from Josh Hazlewood, it was the Indian bowlers' turn to set up the win with the ball.

We reaches its end with everything still to play for on the Gold Coast and in Brisbane, come Saturday.

When: Australia v India, 4th T20I, November 6, 2025, 18:15 hrs Local Time, 19:15 hrs AEDT, 13:45 hrs IST

Where: Gold Coast Stadium (Carrara), Gold Coast

What to expect: There will be no talk of weather around this contest except for it being sunny and excellent on the Gold Coast. After 82,000 packed the MCG last week, there'll be a relatively fewer people in attendance here at Carrara, with the capacity at around 20,000 at this boutique venue. But the hype around this being the Indian men's first game here has been massive enough for us to get another full house. There's a bit of an unknown around how the surface will play here but the boundaries aren't the biggest, and there will be potentially a lot of balls flying in the direction of the crowds.

Team News

Australia

With Travis Head having decided to get some Sheffield Shield action in as part of his conditioning and preparation for the Ashes, there's an opening for Mitch Owen to go up top alongside captain Mitch Marsh. The return of Glenn Maxwell will be a major boost in terms of experience and also quality to the middle order, which looks pretty ominous with his addition. It'll be interesting to see if Mahli Beardman gets a nod in what will be an exciting first look at the young fast bowler at this level.

Probable XI:Mitch Marsh (c), Mitch Owen, Josh Inglis (wk), Glenn Maxwell, Tim David, Marcus Stoinis, Matthew Short, Nathan Ellis, Xavier Bartlett, Matthew Kuhnemann, Mahli Beardman/Ben Dwarshius

India

India rung in the changes after the MCG and it worked out well for them in Hobart with Washington Sundar playing a key role with the bat. Though the top order should remain the same as Shubman Gill continues to try and finish this tour on a high with the bat, the middle order should stay the same too with Jitesh Sharma having impressed with his cameo. ind vs aus t20 highlights. india vs australia t20 highlights. India Cricket Match vs Australia Cricket at Carrara, Cricket Stadium Australia at 1:45 pm IST. 

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav (c), Tilak Varma, Axar Patel, Washington Sundar, Jitesh Sharma (wk)/Sanju Samson, Shivam Dube, Arshdeep Singh, Varun Chakravarthy, Jasprit Bumrah

snippet.title: Nallaru Po Video Song | Dude | Pradeep Ranganathan | @SaiAbhyankkar | Tippu | Keerthiswaran
snippet.description:
Presenting the Video song of 'Nallaru po' from 'Dude', Written & Directed by Keerthiswaran featuring Pradeep Ranganathan, Mamitha Baiju, R.Sarath Kumar, Hridhu Haroon,Rohini, Aishwarya sharma, Dravid selvam & Others.

An @SaiAbhyankkar  Musical 
Song Title: 'Nallaru po'
Album: Dude

Music Credits:

Composed and produced by @SaiAbhyankkar 
Singers: Tipu , @SaiAbhyankkar 
Lyricist : Vivek 
Synth ,keys and Bass programmed by @SaiAbhyankkar 
Acoustic ,Electric Bass Guitar & Charango - Keba 
Navtar - Vishnu Ramprasad 
Violin - Chinmayi 
Live Rhythm - Yanka Rhythm group 
Rhythm produced by @SaiAbhyankkar 

Music Supervisor : Sachin Lal
Music consultant : Adesh krishna 
All recorded and produced at Yolo rechords , engineered by Rajesh Kannan 
Mixed & Masterd by @SaiAbhyankkar 

Movie Credits:

Banner: Mythri Movie Makers
Writer & Director: Keerthiswaran
Producers: Naveen Yerneni, Y Ravi shankar
CO-Producer:  Anil Yerneni
Cinematographer: Niketh Bommi
Production Designer: Latha Naidu
Editor: Barath Vikraman
Action: Yannick ben, Dinesh Subbarayan 
Costume Designer: Poornima Ramaswamy
Art Director: P.L. Subenthar   
VFX supervisors: Ramkumar sundaram 
DI & VFX: Mango post
Colorist: Suresh ravi 
Sound Design: Sync Cinema
Sound Mix: Rajakrishnan M.R
Direction team: Krish Chidambaram, K.C. Perumal, Anirudh Ramesh, Tamilselvan Sankar, Karthick Sekar, Giriprasath, N. Nagaraj
Cinematography team: Yogi Chowdary kotapati, Govinda Rao.P, Dwarak Bharadwaj, Pradeep Raja
Editing Team: Lokesh Raj, Aathieswaran Rajakumar
Art team: Dharma P. Kamalahasan B.F.A, Vaishnavi Ramji, Subiksha Srinivasan, Archana Palani
Stills: M.Dinesh
Publicity Designer:  Viyaki
PRO: Suresh Chandra, Sathish S2Media
Production Controllers : Rangaraj Perumal, E. Suresh Nambiraj
Marketing: First Show
Lyric Video: ADFX


Lyrics:

Nee ketaa unna kooda un kaiyil vittu poguren
Aasa pola vaazhndhukkoyen po
Un mela kaadhal vachene
Thothadhaalum theerala
Ponadhaalum maarala 

Nee ketaa unna kooda un kaiyil vittu poguren
Aasa pola vaazhndhukko di po
Ennalum Kaadhal kuthadhu 
Parvayal Yenga Vechaale 

Paakaama pesaama seraama ponaalum 
Ennaalum nallaru po 
Hey thaangaama thoongaama naan inga vaazhndhaalum
Neeyaachum nallaaru po
 
Kaadhalaa en nenjam
Yekkamaa aanan naane
Kaayamaa nee senjum
Sirikkirene
Yaaradi kutham solla 
En vidhi  enna kolla 
Nee vantha nenjukkulla  
Ippothu onnumilla 

Veroru kayyoda un veral paathen naane 
Vegura nenjoda pogurene
Nethu un kannil naane
Innaikku yaaro dhaane 
Thindaadurene maane
Thaa po nu vittutene 

Paakaama pesaama enkuda seraama ponaalum nallaru po 
Hey thaangaama thoongaama naan inga vaazhndhaalum 
Neeyaachum nallaarupo 

Hey Innoruthanoda nee poga 
Ullolachaloda naan poga 
Enna panna poren Thikku theriyaadhe 
Aanaa neeyum po
 
Hey Ennapanna poren kekaadha
Indha pakkam neeyum paakaadha
Michamulla kaadhal atchadhaya podum 
Nallaa vaazhu po

Hai mana tumhari
Adaa khoobsurat
Tera Ishq bhi hai
Saza khoobsurat
Aankhein tumhaari
Hamein de rahi hain

Nasha khoobsurat
Maza khoobsurat

Tera naam aaya hai
Jabse labon pe
Lage aur bhi ye
Zaban khoobsurat

Mehsoos tumko
Kiya h jinhone
Suna khoobsurat
Kaha khoobsurat

Hai maana...

Jab kagazon pe
Tumko utara
To shayaron ne 
Likha khoobsurat

Jo aake samaya
Wo baahon me teri
Jala khoobsurat
Bujha khoobsurat

Hai maana ...

Ho jaye hasil
Agar dard tera
To lagne lagegi
Dawa khoobsurat

Tu pyaar se bhi
Choole jise vo
Bana khoobsurat
Mita khoobsurat

Hai maana ...

snippet.title: FIDE World Cup 2025 Round 2 Tiebreaks   | Ft.  Pragg, Vidit, Nihal, Pranav
snippet.description:
ChessBase India offer:
The all-new ChessBase'26 and Mega Database'26 is now available for pre-order. 25% off until 10th of November (Use code: FIDEWC)
https://shop.chessbase.in/collections/chessbase-26-and-mega-database-2026-pre-order

Chess.com offer:
World Cup Offer: Get 1 month of Chess.com Premium free by clicking on the link below:
https://go.chess.com/chessbaseindia

The FIDE World Cup 2025 will take place in Goa, India from 1st to 27th of November 2025 and will witness some of the best players in action. The total prize fund of the event is US$2 million with the winner taking home US$1,20,000. There are 3 spots to the Candidates as well at stake.

Format: 
It is a 206-player knockout event. In the first round top 50 seeds get a bye. So it starts with 156 players and comes down to 78 and then the top 50 players join to have 128 players in round 2. There are 2 classical games in each match (90 mins for 40 moves + 30 mins for remaining moves with 30 seconds increment from move 1) and if the score stands at 1-1 then we have the following tiebreaks - 2 games of 15+10, 2 games of 10+10, 2 games of 5+3, 2 games of 3+2, followed by a sudden death which has a time control of 4+2 with special bidding for Black.

Schedule:
Round 1: 1st to 3rd November
Round 2: 4th to 6th November
Round 3: 7th to 9th November
Round 4: 11th to 13th November
Round 5: 14th to 16th November
Round 6: 17th to 19th November
Round 7: 21st to 23rd November
Round 8: 24th to 26th November
Each day the games start at 3 p.m. IST

Commentators:
The commentary panel consists of IM Tania Sachdev, IM Sagar Shah, Amruta Mokal, GM Harshit Raja, GM Sahaj Grover and Sahil Tickoo.

Get the tickets: https://in.bookmyshow.com/sports/fide-world-cup-2025/ET00468629
Pairings: https://worldcup2025.fide.com/tournament-bracket/

https://www.chessbase.in/news/FIDE-World-Cup-2025-Round-1-1-report
